On the other hand, 3 percent of parents said they were bored.
Professor Larson stated that he did not know whether the percentage of boring would now, 21 years later, be higher or lower.
However, he said that he knew that "adolescence is the peak time for boredom", which is largely due to the fact that children and youth are not given much control over what they want to do.
So back to my original question, "Is boring for you?".
As research shows, sometimes not, because in its extreme form it can lead people to take absurd physical risks, play gambling, or abuse addictive substances as a way to alleviate it.
On the other hand, many philosophers and writers discussed the connection between boredom and creativity, said Professor Vodenovich, who studied the problem for over two decades.
"Nuda is a way of the brain to tell you that you should do something else," said Gary Marcus, professor of psychology at NYU.
But the brain doesn't always know the best thing to do.
