However, if you watch television, it will only please you for a while, not for a long time.
So if your child is bored and you give him an iPad, he won't be bored anymore, but he won't learn how to entertain himself or drive himself, Professor Fenske said.
And "this separate procedure is transferred from one situation to another," said the professor.
Your child will not only learn how to entertain himself, but will gain greater self - control in other areas.
I don't think we really want to celebrate boredom.
